name: src/arithmetic/add.js
content: export const add = (a, b) => a + b;

name: src/arithmetic/div.js
content: export const div = (a, b) => a / b;

name: src/arithmetic/divmod.js
content: export const divmod = (a, b) => [(a / b) | 0, a % b];

name: src/arithmetic/idivmod.js
src/arithmetic/mod.js
content: export const mod = (a, b) => a % b;

name: src/arithmetic/mul.js
content: export const mul = (a, b) => a * b;

name: src/arithmetic/shl.js
content: export const shl = (a, n) => a << n;

name: src/arithmetic/shr.js
content: export const shr = (a, n) => a >> n;

name: src/arithmetic/shu.js
content: export const shu = (a, n) => a >>> n;

name: src/arithmetic/special/div2n.js
content: export const div2n = (a, n) => a / 2 ** n;

name: src/arithmetic/sub.js
content: export const sub = (a, b) => a - b;

name: src/compare/decreasing.js
content: export const decreasing = (a, b) => (a > b ? -1 : a === b ? 0 : 1);

name: src/compare/increasing.js
content: export const increasing = (a, b) => (a < b ? -1 : a === b ? 0 : 1);

name: src/index.js
src/logarithmic/log.js
content: export const log = (a, b) => Math.log(b) / Math.log(a);

name: src/logarithmic/loglog.js
content:
export const loglog = (a, b) =>
	Math.log(Math.log(b) / Math.log(a)) / Math.log(a);

name: src/logarithmic/loglog2.js
content: export const loglog2 = (n) => Math.log(Math.log(n) / Math.log(2)) / Math.log(2);

name: src/predicate/eq.js
content: export const eq = (a, b) => a === b;

name: src/predicate/ge.js
content: export const ge = (a, b) => a >= b;

name: src/predicate/gt.js
content: export const gt = (a, b) => a > b;

name: src/predicate/le.js
content: export const le = (a, b) => a <= b;

name: src/predicate/lt.js
content: export const lt = (a, b) => a < b;

name: src/predicate/ne.js
content: export const ne = (a, b) => a !== b;

content:
# Installation

Can be managed using
[jspm](http://jspm.io)
or [npm](https://github.com/npm/npm).

### jspm
```terminal
jspm install npm:@aureooms/js-number
```

### npm
```terminal
npm install @aureooms/js-number --save
```
